-- intended to be used with explicit universe parameters
@[simp]
theorem id_map {C : Cat} {X Y : C} (f : «expr ⟶ » X Y) : ((«expr𝟙») C : «expr ⥤ » C C).map f = f :=
  Functor.id_map f
#align id_map id_map
comp_obj:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
@[simp]
theorem comp_obj {C D E : Cat} (F : «expr ⟶ » C D) (G : «expr ⟶ » D E) (X : C) :
    («expr ≫ » F G).obj X = G.obj (F.obj X) :=
  Functor.comp_obj F G X
#align comp_obj comp_obj
comp_map:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
@[simp]
theorem comp_map {C D E : Cat} (F : «expr ⟶ » C D) (G : «expr ⟶ » D E) {X Y : C} (f : «expr ⟶ » X Y) :
    («expr ≫ » F G).map f = G.map (F.map f) :=
  Functor.comp_map F G f
#align comp_map comp_map
